<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Testing Playground</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Open+Sans:wght@300;400;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="logo">
                <h1>Testing Playground</h1>
                <p>Your Personal Testing Space</p>
            </div>
            <nav>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#features">Features</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
                    <li><a href="#contact">Contact</a></li>
                </ul>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </header>

    <section id="home" class="hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <h1>Welcome to the Testing Playground</h1>
                <p>This is your space to experiment and test various features and ideas.</p>
                <a href="#features" class="btn-primary">Explore Features</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="features" class="features">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Features</h2>
            <div class="feature-grid">
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Interactive Tests</h3>
                    <p>Run interactive tests to check your code and ideas.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Sandbox Environment</h3>
                    <p>A sandbox environment to safely test new features without affecting production.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Documentation</h3>
                    <p>Detailed documentation on how to use the testing tools available.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-card">
                    <h3>Feedback System</h3>
                    <p>A feedback system to help improve and refine your tests.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="about" class="about">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="about-content">
                <h2>About the Testing Playground</h2>
                <p>The Testing Playground is a personal space created to help developers and testers experiment with new ideas, run tests, and improve their skills. It provides an interactive environment where you can safely test your code without any risks.</p>
                <p>We are committed to providing a reliable and secure testing ground for all users. Whether you're a beginner or an experienced developer, the Testing Playground is here to help you achieve your goals.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="contact" class="contact">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Contact Us</h2>
            <div class="contact-content">
                <div class="contact-info">
                    <h3>Get in Touch</h3>
                    <p><strong>Email:</strong> support@testingplayground.com</p>
                    <p><strong>Address:</strong> 456 Test Lane, Play City, PC 67890</p>
                </div>
                <form class="contact-form">
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Your Name" required>
                    <input type="email" placeholder="Your Email" required>
                    <input type="text" placeholder="Subject">
                    <textarea rows="5" placeholder="Your Message" required></textarea>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Send Message</button>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <div class="container">
            <p>&copy; 2023 TestingPlayground.com. All rights reserved.</p>
        </div>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>


